.SH NAME
archive \- file archiving utility with compression and encryption

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B archive
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIARGUMENTS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBarchive\fR is a powerful command-line utility for creating, extracting, 
and managing archive files with support for compression and encryption. 
It provides an easy-to-use interface similar to traditional archiving 
tools like tar and zip, but with modern features and a simple syntax.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBcreate, c\fR
Create a new archive containing specified files and directories.

.TP
\fBextract, x\fR
Extract files from an existing archive to the filesystem.

.TP
\fBlist, l\fR
List the contents of an archive without extracting.

.TP
\fBadd, a\fR
Add files to an existing archive.

.TP
\fBremove, r\fR
Remove files from an existing archive.

.TP
\fBverify, v\fR
Verify the integrity of an archive and its contents.

.TP
\fBupdate, u\fR
Update files in an archive (only if they have changed).

.TP
\fBtest, t\fR
Test an archive for readability and integrity.

.TP
\fBhelp, h\fR
Display help information about commands and options.

.TP
\fBversion, V\fR
Display version information.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v, \-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output, showing more details about operations.

.TP
\fB\-q, \-\-quiet\fR
Enable quiet mode, suppressing all output except errors.

.TP
\fB\-c \fILEVEL\fR, \-\-compression \fILEVEL\fR
Set compression level (0-9). 0 means no compression, 1 is fastest, 
9 is best compression. Default is 6.

.TP
\fB\-p \fIPASSWORD\fR, \-\-password \fIPASSWORD\fR
Set password for encryption/decryption.

.TP
\fB\-n, \-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable progress display during operations.

.TP
\fB\-f \fIFILE\fR, \-\-file \fIFILE\fR
Specify archive filename (alternative syntax).

.TP
\fB\-C \fIDIR\fR, \-\-directory \fIDIR\fR
Change to directory DIR before performing operations.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Create an archive:
archive create backup.arc file1.txt file2.jpg document.pdf

.TP
.B Create encrypted archive:
archive create \-p secret backup.arc sensitive.doc

.TP
.B Extract archive:
archive extract backup.arc

.TP
.B Extract to specific directory:
archive extract backup.arc /tmp/restored

.TP
.B List archive contents:
archive list backup.arc

.TP
.B Add files to archive:
archive add backup.arc newfile.txt

.TP
.B Remove files from archive:
archive remove backup.arc oldfile.txt

.TP
.B Verify archive integrity:
archive verify backup.arc

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, 1 on error.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/archive/default.conf
Default configuration file.

.TP
.I ~/.archiverc
User-specific configuration file.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ARCHIVE_PASSWORD
If set, used as default password for encryption/decryption.

.TP
.B ARCHIVE_COMPRESSION
If set, used as default compression level.

